# 11️⃣ MSTR Environment Template

`templates/mstr-env.yaml.j2`

```yaml
apiVersion: cloud.microstrategy.com/v1
kind: MstrEnvironment

metadata:
  name: {{ mstr_env_name }}
  namespace: {{ namespace }}

spec:
  environmentType: {{ environment_type }}
  environmentSize: {{ environment_size }}
  microstrategyVersion: "{{ microstrategy_version }}"

  imageRegistry: {{ image_registry }}

  dnsEntry: {{ dns_entry }}

  ingressController:
    type: istio
    tlsSecretName: {{ tls_secret }}

  persistentVolumeClaimSpecOverrides:
    resources:
      requests:
        storage: {{ storage_size }}
    storageClassName: {{ storage_class }}

  restoreFrom:
    preset: image

  networkPolicies:
    dnsPort: 5353

  volumePermissions:
    enabled: false
```

---

# 12️⃣ Route Creation

`tasks/route.yml`

```yaml
- name: Get CA bundle
  kubernetes.core.k8s_info:
    api_version: v1
    kind: ConfigMap
    name: openshift-tls-ca
    namespace: "{{ namespace }}"
  register: ca_bundle

- name: Get Istio ingress service
  kubernetes.core.k8s_info:
    api_version: v1
    kind: Service
    namespace: "{{ namespace }}"
    label_selectors:
      - istio=ingressgateway
  register: ingress_svc

- name: Set variables
  set_fact:
    route_ca_cert: "{{ ca_bundle.resources[0].data['ca-bundle.crt'] }}"
    ingress_service: "{{ ingress_svc.resources[0].metadata.name }}"

- name: Create route
  kubernetes.core.k8s:
    state: present
    template: templates/route.yaml.j2
```

---

# 13️⃣ Route Template

`templates/route.yaml.j2`

```yaml
apiVersion: route.openshift.io/v1
kind: Route

metadata:
  name: route-{{ mstr_env_name }}
  namespace: {{ namespace }}

spec:
  host: {{ dns_entry }}

  to:
    kind: Service
    name: {{ ingress_service }}
    weight: 100

  port:
    targetPort: https

  tls:
    termination: reencrypt
    insecureEdgeTerminationPolicy: Redirect
    destinationCACertificate: |
{{ route_ca_cert | indent(6) }}

  wildcardPolicy: None
```

---

# 14️⃣ Wait until environment ready

`tasks/wait_env.yml`

```yaml
- name: Wait for MicroStrategy environment to become READY
  shell: >
    oc get mstrenvironment {{ mstr_env_name }}
    -n {{ namespace }}
    -o jsonpath='{.status.environmentStatus}'
  register: env_status
  retries: 40
  delay: 30
  until: env_status.stdout == "READY"
```

